description:
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to make a difference to the lives of our patients?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting new opportunity has arisen for a Health Care Assistant (Band3) to join the Northwich Care Community based with the Firdale District Nurse Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Health Care Assistants provide skilled care and support to people living in their own home&#39;s and in other community settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do you have an NVQ level3in Health and Social Care or have experience of community work/care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are you passionate about providing high quality, patient focused care along side our Trained Nursing Team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Would you like to learn new clinical care skills including phlebotomy and wound care both at patients own homes and in a clinic environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do you have good communication skills, are you reliable, are you flexible, are you a team player&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be offered bespoke competency based training as well as NHS mandatory training relevant to your role. Support will be provided by registered nurses and experienced Health Care Assistants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thisband3post is for 22.5 hours per week worked over 5 days days for a 7 day service.&lt;/p&gt;
